[Mosquitoes transmit the disease. Horses cannot transmit the disease to people or to other horses. Therefore, there is no need to quarantine the area. This disease is transmitted by mosquitoes.

All horses should be vaccinated against this disease. Horse owners should use fly and mosquito spray labeled for horses. This is an additional layer of protect (and comfort) for your horse.

There is no vaccine against EEE for humans.

The state of Pennsylvania can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at http://healthmap.org/r/3u0d. A county map can be seen at http://www.digital-topo-maps.com/county-map/pennsylvania.shtml. - Mod.TG]
